Admin Dashboard Access Control

The dashboard is protected using:

JWT Authentication
Role-Based Authorization

Only users with:

role = admin

can access admin routes.

Frontend Protection

Frontend route protection uses:

ProtectedRoute

Example:

<ProtectedRoute requiredRole="admin">
  <AdminLayout />
</ProtectedRoute>

ProtectedRoute Responsibilities

Authentication validation
JWT existence validation
Role validation
Dashboard isolation
Unauthorized redirection

The system checks:

access token
stored user object
required role

Unauthorized users are redirected to:

/

User Persistence System

Authenticated user data is stored in:

localStorage

Stored data:

access_token
refresh_token
user

Stored user object includes:

id
username
email
role
profile_image

Benefits:

Avoid unnecessary API requests
Persistent login state
Protected route validation
Role-based UI rendering

